  "text": "To obtain a quicker effect during inhalation induction, a mixture of nitrous oxide and oxygen could be used as a carrier gas in children without contraindications; in the remaining cases, 100% oxygen or a mixture of oxygen and air can be administered. The advantages of inhalation induction include painlessness and reversibility, while the disadvantages are the risk of laryngospasm and higher incidence of transient postoperative agitation [CITATION_1] .",
